---
// input: siteConfig data, related guides list layout component
// output: Offline Cash guide page showing board optimization and locking shield protection
// pos: src/pages/offline-cash.astro (更新规则：文件变更需同步本注释与所属目录 README)

import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RelatedGuides from "../components/RelatedGuides.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../data/config";
---

<SiteLayout title="Merge a Nuke Guide Offline Cash | Roblox Idle Setup" description="Maximize your idle income with the Merge a Nuke guide offline cash setup. Learn to optimize hangar weapons and activate base lock shields.">
  <main class="content-page">
    <section class="prose-block" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Offline cash</p>
      <h1>{siteConfig.gameName} Offline Cash Guide</h1>
      <p>Offline cash generation is the foundation of long-term tycoon progression in Roblox Merge a Nuke. By setting up your board correctly and protecting your assets before logging off, you can secure millions of passive dollars during away-from-keyboard windows. This page explains how to build the perfect idle cash setup.</p>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(46, 213, 115, 0.05); border: 1.5px solid rgba(46, 213, 115, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-interactive); line-height: 1.6;">
        <h3 style="color: var(--color-green); margin-bottom: 8px;">Offline Cash Strategy Rationale</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Logging off with a cluttered board or an unlocked base is a recipe for stalled progression. Opponents can raid your base while you are offline, reset your progress, and siphon your stored currency. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> provides a step-by-step checklist to keep your earnings safe and maximize your idle accumulation rates.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="offline-optimization" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pre-logout steps</p>
      <h2 id="offline-optimization" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Idle income optimization loop</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.6;">Your offline cash output is determined entirely by the active weapons sitting in your hangar when you close the Roblox client. Leaving duplicates on the grid instead of merging them upwards limits your passive income capacity. Follow these optimization steps before every logout.</p>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Merging up before logging out</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Never leave two identical missile tiers unmerged on your board when logging off. A single higher-tier weapon generates significantly more cash per minute than two lower-tier duplicates. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> recommends performing a complete grid cleanup, matching all possible duplicates to place your absolute best warheads in your active hangar slots.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Additionally, clean up early-tier debris. Spawner systems continue to run locally, but a cluttered board leaves no space for incoming spawner drops during your next active play session. Clear the workspace to prepare your tycoon for an immediate cash boost upon your return.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Activating base locking shields</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">An unlocked base is a target for the entire server. If an opponent attacks your base while you are offline, your accumulated passive cash will be siphoned and your weapon progression stalled. Activating the base lock shield is the final, essential step before closing the game client.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> emphasizes upgrading your base shield duration to match your away windows. A secure base lock shield ensures that your idle income compounds without interruption, safeguarding your milestones and letting you return to a massive cash pile.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section grid-section" aria-labelledby="reinvestment-loop" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Reinvestment</p>
        <h2 id="reinvestment-loop">Return and reinvestment loop</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Collecting accumulated idle cash</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">When you log back in, collect your accumulated offline cash immediately. This pocket cash is vulnerable to raids if you stay in the active server lobby without checking your defenses. Reinvesting this currency immediately secures its value.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> recommends spending at least 80% of your collected offline cash on permanent attributes, such as spawn speed and board slot expansions, before you look for PvP targets or join community discussions.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Spend offline returns on permanent upgrades to convert liquid cash into permanent progress.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Avoiding multiplier decay gaps</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Some server updates can reset active multiplier coefficients. Keep an eye on weekly Wednesday and Friday developer logs. If your cash output rate feels lower than expected after a patch, it means a balance change has occurred.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Following this <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> help forum will keep you updated on any multiplier adjustments. Adjust your merging layouts to align with the latest balance changes, ensuring that your idle income remains optimal through every version shift.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Stay updated on weekly developer logs to keep your layouts aligned with active multiplier rates.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedGuides currentSlug="offline-cash" />
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
